  "text": "Renal morphology was analyzed using light microscopy. The kidney tissue was fixed in 10% neutral buffered formalin, embedded in paraffin, cut into 3 m sections, and stained with periodic-acidSchiff (PAS). After PAS staining, the degree of glomerular sclerosis was assessed on a semiquantitative scale: grade 0, all glomeruli normal; grade 1, sclerotic area up to 25% (minimal sclerosis); grade 2, sclerotic area 25-50% (moderate sclerosis); grade 3, sclerotic area 50-75% (moderate-to-severe sclerosis); grade 4, sclerotic area 75-100% (severe sclerosis). One hundred glomeruli in each group were examined using that semiquantitative scale, as previously described [CITATION_1] . The glomerulosclerosis index (GSI) was calculated using the following formula:",
